Author Albert Murray said of the relationship of the town to the novel -LRB- and the annual performance -RRB- : `` It becomes part of the town ritual , like the religious underpinning of Mardi Gras .
With the whole town crowded around the actual courthouse , it 's part of a central , civic education -- what Monroeville aspires to be . ''
